            <title>[HBASE-12001] Provide additional option to calculate actual object size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-12001</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;(May be it was discussed elsewhere and I missed it, in that case I&apos;m sorry &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; )&lt;br/&gt;
Currently there&apos;s HeapSize interface, marked as the one useful to measure caches, and some implementation thereof computing the sizes of different objects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was thinking to add something like &lt;a href=&quot;https://code.google.com/p/memory-measurer/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://code.google.com/p/memory-measurer/&lt;/a&gt; and provide sort of default implementation of HeapSize which can measure the size of arbitrary objects in bytes. Would require a javaagent to be hooked up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
